==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æm|-æm]]

===Noun===
'''sham'''

# A fake, an imitation that purports to be genuine.
#: ''the time-share deal was a sham''
# Trickery, hoaxing.
#: ''a con-man must be skilled in the arts of sham and deceit''
# A decorative cover for a pillow.

